<TITLE> Rajshahi reports first swine flu case after Sylhet, Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com)--A swine flu patient on Friday was admitted to Rajshahi Contagious Diseases Hospital, a doctor said, in a third case reported outside Dhaka. Saifuddin Ekram, a specialist doctor at the hospital, told bdnews24.com Shamim Ara, a family planning worker in Mohonpur Upazila in Rajshahi,was admitted to the hospital at noon with fever, runny nose and cough. On initial symptoms, he was being treated as a swine flu patient. The prime minister's health affairs advisor Syed Modasser Ali visited the patient in the afternoon. Ekram told him that a team of 15-20 doctors was ready at the hospital for swine flu patients. Ali expressed happiness over the readiness. Ali suggested that people should not to take swine flu drugs without prescription from the doctor. An air force officer and a doctor were the first confirmed swine flu cases in Chittagong and Sylhet. Flight Lieutenant Tanvirul Islam is under treatment in Chittagong air force hospital. IEDCR tests confirmed the H1N1 virus on Tuesday. The first case of swine flu was detected in Sylhet on Monday, said Najmul Islam, principal of Ragib Rabeya Medical College Hospital. Mohammad Idris Ali, a medical officer of the hospital's Paediatric Department, tested positive after samples were sent to IEDCR in Dhaka. bdn
